api_list.code:
import requests

url = "https://mitchelljames-onsched-v1.p.rapidapi.com/consumer/v1/customers/countries"

headers = {
            "X-RapidAPI-Key": "SIGN-UP-FOR-KEY",
            "X-RapidAPI-Host": "mitchelljames-onsched-v1.p.rapidapi.com"
        }

response = requests.get(url, headers=headers)
print(response.json())

api_list.name: Customer Custom Fields
api_list.description: This end point returns your Customer custom field definitions.  Customer custom fields are different than Appointment custom fields. Appointment custom fields are stored with each appointment. They are used when the information collected during the booking is specific to a particular visit, where as Customer custom fields are stored with the customer profile.

optional_parameters.name: locationId
optional_parameters.description: The id of the business location. Defaults to first business location.

optional_parameters.name: leadQuestions
optional_parameters.description: A true/false indicator to filter on custom fields used for lead questions.

api_list.name: Customer Booking Fields
api_list.description: This end point returns Booking Field definitions.  Customer booking fields are different than Appointment booking fields. Customer booking fields are stored with each customer. They are used when the information collected during the booking is specific to a particular visit.

optional_parameters.name: locationId
optional_parameters.description: The id of the business location. Defaults to first business location.
